      <title>Building a Knowledge Graph</title>
      <link>http://localhost:55541/articles/building-a-knowledge-graph/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 03 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:55541/articles/building-a-knowledge-graph/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The knowledge graph visualizes connections between notes. It turns the abstract idea of &amp;ldquo;linked thinking&amp;rdquo; into something you can see and explore.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;why-visualize&#34;&gt;Why Visualize?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Our brains are visual. A list of backlinks tells you &lt;em&gt;what&lt;/em&gt; connects, but a graph shows you &lt;em&gt;how&lt;/em&gt; the connections form patterns.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure class=&#34;admonition not-prose rounded-lg p-4 mb-4 border-l-4 bg-blue-50 border-blue-500 dark:bg-blue-900/20 dark:border-blue-400&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;figcaption class=&#34;flex items-center gap-2 font-semibold mb-2 text-gray-900 dark:text-white&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; class=&#34;w-5 h-5 text-blue-500&#34;&gt;&lt;circle cx=&#34;12&#34; cy=&#34;12&#34; r=&#34;10&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M12 16v-4&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M12 8h.01&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&lt;span&gt;Try It&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prose dark:prose-invert prose-sm max-w-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;    Open the &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:55541/graph/&#34;&gt;full-page graph&lt;/a&gt; to explore. Drag nodes, filter by section, toggle link types.&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-it-works&#34;&gt;How It Works&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The graph uses D3.js force simulation. Each note becomes a node; each link becomes an edge.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
